# Naming conventions

## C#

- Files: PascalCase (`ConfirmAppointmentCommand.cs`)
- Interfaces: `I` + PascalCase (`IPaymentGateway`, `ISearchService`)
- Async methods: `Async` suffix (`GetByIdAsync`, `DispatchNotificationAsync`)
- `CancellationToken`: always named `ct`, always last parameter
- MediatR requests: `record` types preferred
- DTOs: suffix `Dto` (`AppointmentDetailsDto`)
- Hangfire jobs: suffix `Job` (`OutboxProcessorJob`)
- SignalR hubs: suffix `Hub` (`TelemedicineHub`, `QueueHub`)
- EF configurations: suffix `Configuration` (`AppointmentConfiguration`)
- Domain events: suffix `DomainEvent` (`AppointmentConfirmedDomainEvent`)
- Error codes: `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE` (`PRESCRIPTION_EXPIRED`, `SLOT_UNAVAILABLE`)

## Other stacks

- Python: `snake_case` files/functions; PascalCase classes; Pydantic models suffix `Request`/`Response`
- Flutter/Dart: PascalCase widgets/classes; camelCase variables/functions
- Next.js: PascalCase components; camelCase hooks (`useAppointments.ts`)

