# Code style rules

## C# 12+

- Primary constructors, collection expressions, pattern matching
- Prefer `record` for commands, queries, DTOs, domain events
- File-scoped namespaces in all C# files
- Nullable reference types enabled (`<Nullable>enable</Nullable>`); treat as errors in Domain + Application
- Never suppress nullable with `!` without a comment explaining why
- Guard clauses over deep nesting
- Maximum method length: 40 lines; maximum class length: 200 lines
- All I/O async — never `.Result` or `.Wait()`
- Pass `CancellationToken` (`ct`) through the full call chain
- `ILogger<T>` via constructor injection — never static loggers
- Never log PHI in plaintext; include `trace_id` in log messages
- Use `DateTime.UtcNow` for timestamps — never `DateTime.Now`
- Parameterise all SQL — never string concatenation into queries
- Never use AutoMapper — explicit mapping extension methods
- **Magic values:** centralize durations, thresholds, and policy constants (or load from configuration) — especially when tied to P-properties or compliance.

## Python

- Type hints on all signatures; Pydantic v2 throughout; `async def` on FastAPI endpoints; read-only DB access; no raw dicts in endpoint signatures

